Commentary: OUT! WHAT A GRAB! Matt Henry strikes with his first delivery! A disaster for Clyde Fortuin as he goes for a golden duck! Henry starts from over the wicket and pitches it up to the batter, inviting him to go for the drive, outside off, Clyde Fortuin falls for the trap and reaches out in front. He does not move his feet and goes at it with hard hands. Gets an outside edge that flies waist-high to the left of gully. Glenn Phillips reacts quickly and flings his left hand to pluck it out of thin air. Phillips makes a tough catch look easy and New Zealand have the early wicket.

Commentary: OUT! Given LBW! A big shout and up goes the finger! Raynard van Tonder walks up to his partner and Neil Brand goes for the review! William bowls it with an upright seam from around the wicket, on a good length, on off and middle, Neil Brand does not move his feet much and looks to keep it out with a straight bat. The ball nips back in off the deck and sneaks past the inside edge to rap him high on the back leg. There is nothing on UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking shows that it has pitched in line, the impact is in line and wickets is umpire's call as it is clipping the middle stump. William O'Rourke gets his first Test wicket and what a special moment it is for the debutant. The skipper, Neil Brand walks back dejected who was looking good.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Oh, no! What have you done, Zubayr Hamza? He runs out of patience and throws his wicket away! Spin has done the trick for New Zealand. Rachin Ravindra tosses it up nicely and invites the big shot, full and around off, Zubayr Hamza clears his front leg and gets down. His eyes light up and goes for an ugly hoick across the line. The ball spins away and catches the top edge and it lobs tamely to backward point where the substitute fielder, Mitchell Santner takes it.

Commentary: Was it a bump ball? Hang on a minute, it does not look so, and David Bedingham looks to be gone here. Yes, he surely is. Unfortunate for Bedingham and New Zealand are delighted. Rachin hurls it on a fullish length, on middle, David Bedingham keeps his weight on the back foot and looks to clip it away on the leg side. Gets an inside edge that goes straight onto his boot and pops up in the hands of Will Young at short leg. At first instance, it looked like a bump ball and the ball had bounced off the ground. Moreover, Young had flicked the ball back to the keeper to attempt a run out so he was not sure either. As it turns out, a lucky breakthrough for New Zealand.

Commentary: OUT! CHOPPED ON! It's William O'Rourke again! End of Ruan de Swardt's long vigil. It deflects onto his heels before trickling back onto the stumps to dislodge the bails. The debutant gets his third wicket and South Africa lose their ninth wicket with 242 runs on the board.

Howout: b William O'Rourke

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Two in two from the debutant, William O'Rourke to wrap up the innings. Dane Paterson goes for a big shot first up and perishes. William O'Rourke comes from over the wicket for the right-hander and bowls it on a good length, angling in, around middle and leg, Dane Paterson backs away a long way on the leg side and swings through the line. The ball comes on slower than he expected and he ends up slicing it high in the air off the bottom half of the bat. It goes up only as far as second slip as where Tom Latham settles under it and dives forward to take the catch safely. William O'Rourke finishes with 4 wickets and South Africa have been bowled out for 242 in their first innings.
Default_Commentary: 97.2: William O'Rourke to Dane Paterson, OUT! c Tom Latham b William O'Rourke.
Howout: c Tom Latham b William O'Rourke

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! It's Dane Piedt again! A rush of blood for Will Young and he pays the price for it. South Africa are jubilant as they find themselves right on top. Piedt gives the ball air and bowls it full, on off and middle, Will Young shimmies down the track and tries to go down town with the spin. The bat turns in his hands and he fails to get the desired connection. Hits it flat and straight down the throat of wide long on where Ruan de Swardt reverse cups it in front of his face. A body blow to New Zealand as they lose their last recognised batter with still 79 runs away from parity.
